+ <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’) and <i>Rannulf</i> (from <i>hraf(a)n</i> ‘raven’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’).","History: An American family bearing this surname are descended from William Randolph (<i>c.</i> 1651–1711), a planter and merchant, a member of a family that originally came from Sussex, England. William Randolph emigrated from Warwickshire to VA <i>c.</i> 1673. He was a forebear of Thomas Jefferson and Robert E. Lee. Randolph had seven sons, each of whom inherited an estate, the name of which was sometimes added to their own, such as Sir John Randolph of Tazewell. His great-grandsons included Edmund Randolph (1753–1813), first attorney general of the US and one of the framers of the US Constitution, and the diplomat and statesman John Randolph of Roanoke (1773–1833), who served as US minister to Russia."]},{"name":"Rendall","meanings":["English: variant of   Randall  .","Scottish: habitational name from Rendall (Orkney), named with a stream-name of uncertain origin + Old Norse <i>dalr</i> ‘valley’.","In some cases possibly also an Americanized form of Swedish   Rendahl  ."]}]},{"name":"Ragnvald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old Norse personal name <i>Rögnvaldr</i>, from <i>regin</i> ‘advice, decision’ (also, ‘the gods’) + <i>valdr</i> ‘ruler’. Compare  Ronald  ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"av","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ragnvald Kolbeinnson av Randall was born in 1405, in Kirkwall, Orkney, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Mr Kolbein av Randall, was 27 and his mother, Mrs. Kolbein Randall, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Ragnvald de Randall. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"1405–":"1405–Surnud","1405–Male":"1405–Surnud","1407–Female":"1407–Surnud","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1378–1436":"1378–1436","1381–Female":"1381–Sur